Undid revision 894212562 by [[Special:Contributions/Serenwyl|Serenwyl]] ([[User talk:Serenwyl|talk]]) The illegal taking of a kestral is relevent in the context of Mr Packham's development as a wildlife enthusiast and TV presenter; is it also relevent given his public position on the killing and taking of wild birds referenced in the "general licence" section elsewhere in the entry.

Undid revision 894511095 by [[Special:Contributions/Serenwyl|Serenwyl]] ([[User talk:Serenwyl|talk]]). There is no sound reason for removing this information. It is key to Mr Packham's career that he is seen as an expert on environmental matters; his promotion of a product that does not stand up to scrutiny of its environmental credentials is therefore directly relevent to Mr Packham's public and professional image.

Undid revision 894511154 by [[Special:Contributions/Serenwyl|Serenwyl]] ([[User talk:Serenwyl|talk]]) The scaling of a bus shelter is corew to the purpose of the Extinction Rebellion, that being to disrupt the normal functioning of London, and to use extreme acts to draw attention to the protestor's cause.
/* Views */  Additional information added on purpose of GLs.

Extinction Rebellion's website describes its intentions to be "blockading the city, engaging in civil disobedience, taking direct action": this is disruptive behaviour; indeed, disruption is the entire point.  His climbing ona  public bs shelter is widely reported by media including ITV News and there is no reason to supress this action.
The Belfast telegraph (est. 1870) and the BBC are legitimate, reliable and widely respected sources.
